# UI, Components, and UX Rules

- Prefer existing shadcn/ui components before creating custom primitives.
- Keep styling in Tailwind utility classes and project tokens/CSS variables.
- Build for mobile and desktop verification flows; avoid desktop-only interactions.
- Use consistent states for async actions: idle, loading, success, error.
- For AI extraction and upload operations, include skeleton/loading feedback.
- For errors, use in-app modals/toasts/surfaces; never use browser alerts.
- Favor clarity over decoration in handoff views: progress-to-close, verification badges, and audit visibility must stay prominent.
